40:52.657 --> 40:54.935
For years here,
the base was what was called

40:54.969 --> 40:56.315
a West Virginia Democrat:

40:56.350 --> 40:58.490
hard line
on the second amendment,

40:58.525 --> 41:00.216
religious, but pro-union,

41:00.250 --> 41:02.701
with a record of voting
reliably blue.

41:02.736 --> 41:05.877
Those days are gone.

41:05.911 --> 41:07.844
You know,
I'm a high school dropout.

41:07.879 --> 41:09.777
Military, you know,
I was... I'm a veteran.

41:09.812 --> 41:13.505
There is a smell in the earth
itself here in West Virginia

41:13.540 --> 41:16.474
that, when I was away,
when I was in the army,

41:16.508 --> 41:18.821
that your soul rots away.

41:18.855 --> 41:20.685
It feels like you can't
smell it, or you look up

41:20.719 --> 41:23.550
and you see the sun
all the way set.

41:23.584 --> 41:26.000
Here it disappears around 4:00.

41:26.035 --> 41:29.314
Allen Lardieri is a former
tanker in the U.S. Army

41:29.348 --> 41:33.076
and what he calls
Constitutional Conservative.

41:33.111 --> 41:35.665
He is solidly
pro-Trump Republican,

41:35.700 --> 41:38.219
however distant from
Mr. Trump's New York City

41:38.254 --> 41:41.326
background and gold-plated
lifestyle he may be.

41:41.360 --> 41:43.742
You'll see a lot of parallels
in rural West Virginia

41:43.777 --> 41:45.744
that you see
in the inner cities.

41:45.779 --> 41:48.229
I see a lot of parallels
to places I've been.

41:48.264 --> 41:49.886
School districts
that are starved.

41:49.921 --> 41:51.336
- That's right.
- Opioid addiction.

41:51.370 --> 41:52.337
Teenage pregnancy.

41:52.371 --> 41:53.752
Food deserts, you know,

41:53.787 --> 41:55.264
where there ain't nothing
but fast food.

41:55.271 --> 41:58.585
Exactly. Okay.
Yeah. Where's our Whole Foods?

41:58.619 --> 42:00.172
It's non-existent, sir.

42:00.207 --> 42:05.453
Why would West Virginia
overwhelmingly go for a guy,

42:05.488 --> 42:09.078
Donald Trump, who's never
changed a tire in his life,

42:09.112 --> 42:11.080
who sits on a gold toilet?

42:11.114 --> 42:14.773
Yeah, everybody else
talks around this, whatever.

42:14.808 --> 42:16.948
This man talks just like us,

42:16.982 --> 42:18.708
like how we talk
to each other in the mines.

42:18.743 --> 42:20.952
It ain't pretty.
It's straight talk.

42:20.986 --> 42:23.126
Well, you know, they say
he tells it like it is.

42:23.161 --> 42:25.128
I don't know... I don't
know that that's true.

42:25.163 --> 42:26.682
He says outrageous things.

42:26.716 --> 42:28.124
I guess that's refreshing.
Oh, yeah.

42:28.131 --> 42:29.401
You know, I gave up
on political saviors

42:29.408 --> 42:30.789
a long time ago.

42:30.824 --> 42:32.480
I believe it's naive
to go ahead and say

42:32.515 --> 42:34.337
that I think that there's
gonna be one individual,

42:34.344 --> 42:35.622
especially in government,

42:35.656 --> 42:37.382
that's gonna turn
everything around.

42:37.416 --> 42:39.591
Trump can bring change,
and it's very quite simple.

42:39.626 --> 42:43.215
His offensive, incendiary nature

42:43.250 --> 42:45.252
can send a word out
to these assholes...

42:45.286 --> 42:48.496
I'm sorry... these individuals
that so called represent us

42:48.531 --> 42:49.946
in congress, senate, whatever.

42:49.981 --> 42:52.155
If people get frustrated enough,

42:52.190 --> 42:55.262
they're gonna put somebody
in there that's not like you.

42:55.296 --> 42:56.988
You know, what I hope
that things

42:57.022 --> 42:59.956
have come out of this
is national dialogue.

42:59.991 --> 43:02.959
We have to start talking.
We have to do it.

43:02.994 --> 43:04.961
If he'd stop tweeting
from the toilet at 4:00

43:04.996 --> 43:06.749
in the morning, I'd feel
a lot more comfortable,

43:06.756 --> 43:08.910
you know what I'm saying?
A little impulse control, dude.

43:24.394 --> 43:24.894
♪

43:33.990 --> 43:35.675
These right here,
they're called wood nettle.

43:35.682 --> 43:40.203
They've got a really nice kind
of aromatic quality to them.

43:40.238 --> 43:42.205
♪

43:42.240 --> 43:44.173
With the pawpaws, it's better

43:44.207 --> 43:45.968
if you can kind of,
like, feel them,

43:46.002 --> 43:47.625
see if they're ripe.

43:47.659 --> 43:51.352
America's forgotten fruit:
the pawpaw.

43:51.387 --> 43:53.216
Forgotten when most Americans

43:53.251 --> 43:55.529
stopped going to the forest
for their food,

43:55.563 --> 43:58.843
but in West Virginia,
they were never forgotten.

43:58.877 --> 44:02.881
So that's a pawpaw ice cream
with some candied wildflowers,

44:02.916 --> 44:05.056
and then this is
an old-fashioned vinegar pie.

44:05.090 --> 44:08.162
It's in a class of pies
called desperation pies

44:08.197 --> 44:10.233
that try to create
something like a lemon pie

44:10.268 --> 44:12.166
and you don't have lemon juice.
What do you do?

44:12.201 --> 44:14.065
Put some vinegar
and some nutmeg together

44:14.099 --> 44:16.377
and give it that same
kind of tang.

44:16.412 --> 44:20.036
Appalachia has a rich
and deep culinary culture,

44:20.071 --> 44:22.245
increasingly fetishized,
riffed on,

44:22.280 --> 44:25.593
appropriated for the genteel
tastes of a hipster elite

44:25.628 --> 44:29.080
willing to pay big bucks
for what used to be,

44:29.114 --> 44:31.979
and still is in many cases,
the food of poverty.

44:32.014 --> 44:34.602
We see that ramps are selling
for $30 a pound

44:34.637 --> 44:37.536
in New York City that were
harvested in West Virginia,

44:37.571 --> 44:40.056
and what's West Virginia
seeing from that?

44:40.091 --> 44:43.266
Probably a guy that got
about 2 bucks a pound.

44:43.301 --> 44:45.993
It becomes just another
extractive industry.

44:46.028 --> 44:47.823
- Right.
- Like coal or timber.

44:47.857 --> 44:49.196
And you sort of start
to see that with foods.

44:49.203 --> 44:50.473
That's the story
of West Virginia.

44:50.480 --> 44:52.034
Yeah.

44:52.068 --> 44:54.450
Chef Mike Costello
and partner Amy Dawson

44:54.484 --> 44:57.729
are looking to keep that
culture alive and appreciated

44:57.764 --> 45:00.939
and paying off locally for
the region it originated in.

45:00.974 --> 45:02.700
I also have some buttermilk
poached trout

45:02.734 --> 45:05.047
that we're gonna put on there
